\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
Going back to the weak form for the original infinite dimensional problem,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\int_{\Omega}\nabla\phi\cdot\nabla\psi\: dV=\int_{\Omega}\phi f\: dV+\int_{\delta\Omega^{N}}\phi b\: dV,
\]

\end_inset

it is obvious that 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\nabla\psi$
\end_inset

 must be well behaved enough for these integrals to exist.
 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Separator

\end_layout

