\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
We require the function is square integrable,
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left\Vert \psi\right\Vert ^{2}:=\int_{\Omega}\psi^{2}\: dV<\infty.
\end{equation}

\end_inset

(The space of function which satisfy this is normally called 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{L}_{2}\left(\Omega\right)$
\end_inset

) and also that
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\left\Vert \nabla\psi\right\Vert ^{2}:=\int_{\Omega}\nabla\psi\cdot\nabla\psi\: dV<\infty,
\end{equation}

\end_inset

Functions which satisfy both (1) & (2) are in the space of square integrable
 functions with square integrable derivatives, denoted 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{H}^{1}\left(\Omega\right)$
\end_inset

.
 This is a 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
emph{Sobolev space}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
